    "top_event": "Hand injury from falling container during crane lift operation",
    "incident_type": "Struck by object / Crane lifting accident",
    "costs": null,
    "actions_taken": [
      "Injured employee transported to medical facility",
      "Onsite investigation conducted on 16-APR-2018",
      "8 stitches administered for laceration"
    ],
    "summary": "On April 12, 2018 at 1530 hours, an employee suffered a laceration to the back of his left hand when a trash storage container fell during a crane lifting operation. The container broke away from the deck and began to fall toward the signalman after becoming stuck with the trash bag. A piece of angle iron from the container frame struck the employee's hand. The incident occurred because the signalman left the sight of the crane operator without proper communication, the crane operator continued the lift without visual confirmation of the signalman, and the signalman was not wearing gloves.",
    "recommendations": [],
